# Search bar alignment math

In `FloatingSearch.swift`, the note title starts at 8pt (`.padding(.horizontal, 8)`) + 15pt (icon frame) + 8pt (HStack spacing) = 31pt from the VStack's leading edge. Preview text and folder pill padding must use `.padding(.leading, 31)` to align flush with the first character of the title.

**Why:** Was originally `.padding(.leading, 36)` which caused a visible 5pt misalignment between the title and the folder pill / preview text below it. Fixed 2026-04-06.

**How to apply:** If adding new rows to search result items, use 31pt leading padding to match the title alignment. If the icon width or HStack spacing changes, recalculate: `horizontal_padding + icon_width + hstack_spacing`.
